N:task-estimation
D:Turn vague backlog items, stories, bugs, spikes, roadmap slices, or milestone work into practical size signals, uncertainty notes, and forecast-safe estimate packets. Use when the user needs story points, t-shirt sizing, planning-poker prep, reference-story calibration, or risk framing without turning estimates into deadlines.
G:task-estimation story-points t-shirt-sizing planning-poker roadmap-forecasting agile

U[5]:
  Estimate a backlog item, bug, feature slice, spike, or milestone task
  Choose between story points, t-shirt sizing, planning-poker prep, or a rough forecast packet
  Calibrate work against reference stories instead of guessing in isolation
  Surface uncertainty, dependencies, and split recommendations
  Produce a commitment-safe estimate packet rather than a deadline

X[3]:
  backlog decomposition or readiness shaping -> task-planning
  daily blocker cadence or execution sync -> standup-meeting
  completed-work process reflection -> sprint-retrospective

S[5]{n,action}:
  1,Triage the estimate mode
  2,Pick the lightest useful estimation frame
  3,Estimate relative to reference work and visible uncertainty
  4,Build an estimate packet with confidence and blockers
  5,Separate planning signal from commitment

R[5]:
  choose the smallest useful estimation frame
  keep uncertainty and split signals visible
  avoid fake precision when scope is vague
  route non-estimation work to neighboring PM skills
  end with a recommended next move
